# Cool Numbers Checker

This Java program finds all "cool numbers" between two bounds `a` and `b`.  
A number is considered cool if all its non-zero digits divide evenly into a given number `n`.

## Features
- Checks if individual numbers are "cool"
- Counts all cool numbers in a given range
- Prints them to the console

## Skills Used
- Java
- Loops and conditionals
- Number theory logic
- Input validation and digit extraction

## How to Run
Compile and run using any Java IDE or terminal:

```bash
javac CoolNumbers.java
java CoolNumbers
